"script": "The glass bottle in your hand was once a pile of ordinary beach sand. First, that sand is mixed with crushed recycled glass and heated to nearly 3,000 degrees. Then it melts into a glowing orange blob, thick and gooey like honey. And a machine snips off a perfect droplet, dropping it straight into a bottle-shaped mold. Next, a blast of air inflates the blob from the inside, pressing it against the walls like a balloon. Finally, the bottle cools slowly so it doesn't crack, hardening back into the clear glass you toss away without a thought.",
